# Supabase — Production Observability Reference

---

## Log Drains (Pro plan — available March 2026)

Log Drains stream all Supabase logs to your monitoring service in real time.
Covers: Edge Function logs, PostgREST API logs, Auth logs, Realtime logs, Storage logs.

```
Dashboard → Settings → Log Drains → Add drain
```

### Datadog setup
```
Destination type: Datadog
Endpoint: https://http-intake.logs.datadoghq.com/api/v2/logs
Headers:
  DD-API-KEY: [your Datadog API key]
  Content-Type: application/json

Service name: supabase-[project-name]
Source: supabase
```

### Axiom setup (recommended — generous free tier)
```
Destination type: HTTP
Endpoint: https://api.axiom.co/v1/datasets/[dataset-name]/ingest
Headers:
  Authorization: Bearer [axiom-api-token]
  Content-Type: application/json
```

### S3 / R2 archive
```
Destination type: S3
Bucket: your-log-archive-bucket
Region: us-east-1
Access Key ID: [AWS or Cloudflare R2 access key]
Secret Access Key: [secret]
Prefix: supabase-logs/        # organizes logs by date automatically
```

### OTLP (OpenTelemetry — for Grafana, Honeycomb, etc.)
```
Destination type: OTLP
Endpoint: https://otlp.nr-data.net:4317   # New Relic example
Headers:
  api-key: [New Relic license key]
```

