## Prometheus Metrics API

Supabase exposes ~200 Postgres performance metrics via a Prometheus-compatible endpoint.
Completely separate from Log Drains — raw numeric series for charting and alerting.

### Endpoint
```
GET https://api.supabase.com/platform/projects/{ref}/analytics/endpoints/prometheus
Authorization: Bearer [SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN]
```

### Key metrics to monitor

```
# Database connections
supabase_pg_stat_activity_count           # total active connections
supabase_pg_stat_database_numbackends     # backends per database

# Query performance
supabase_pg_stat_statements_total_time    # total query execution time
supabase_pg_stat_statements_calls         # query call count

# Storage
supabase_pg_database_size_bytes           # database size in bytes
supabase_pg_statio_user_tables_heap_blks_read  # disk reads (high = needs indexes)

# Replication / WAL
supabase_pg_replication_slots_active      # active replication slots
supabase_pg_stat_replication_sent_lag     # WAL send lag (for read replicas)
```

### Grafana scrape config
```yaml
# prometheus.yml
scrape_configs:
  - job_name: supabase
    scheme: https
    bearer_token: [SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN]
    static_configs:
      - targets: ['api.supabase.com']
    metrics_path: /platform/projects/[PROJECT_REF]/analytics/endpoints/prometheus
    scrape_interval: 60s      # Supabase recommends no faster than 60s
```

### Critical alert rules
```yaml
# alerts.yml — add to Grafana/Prometheus alertmanager
groups:
  - name: supabase
    rules:
      - alert: HighConnectionCount
        expr: supabase_pg_stat_activity_count > 150   # 75% of free tier limit
        for: 5m
        annotations:
          summary: "DB connections approaching limit ({{ $value }} active)"

      - alert: DatabaseSizeWarning
        expr: supabase_pg_database_size_bytes > 419430400   # 400MB of 500MB free limit
        annotations:
          summary: "Database at 80% capacity ({{ $value | humanize1024 }})"

      - alert: SlowQueries
        expr: rate(supabase_pg_stat_statements_total_time[5m]) > 1000
        annotations:
          summary: "High query execution time detected"
```

